# NetBSD architectures with no official prebuilt pkgsrc binaries.
#
# Unlike the FreeBSD repo (poudriere + qemu-user-static), these are built
# inside a full-system SIMH emulator, because no qemu-user backend exists
# for these CPUs. Each line therefore describes the SIMH machine, not a
# binfmt/qemu interpreter.
#
# Space-separated fields, one architecture per line:
#
#   <arch> <simh_binary> <disk_type>
#
#   arch         MACHINE_ARCH / pkgsrc arch; also the disk-image arch name
#                used by netbsd-builder (e.g. vax).
#   simh_binary  Name of the SIMH simulator that runs this arch (e.g. vax).
#   disk_type    SIMH RQ0 disk type the image was built with (e.g. RA92).
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
vax vax RA92
